description: A row over French boats' access to Guernsey waters was caused by rule changes, a politician claims.
title: Guernsey-France fishing dispute caused by Brexit confusion
title_page: Guernsey-France fishing dispute caused by Brexit confusion - BBC News
maintext: Mr Le Tocq said the disruption had been caused by the fact Guernsey was informed "only 10 days" before 31 January that it was not covered by EU regulation and it would be illegal for French fisherman to operate there.
